      "date": "2011-05-09 20:10:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nSorry, my mistake.  I didn't read the commit message closely enough.  Alphabetized by the short option letter is fine too.\n\nOn a related note, there are a number of other sub-commands in lfs (e.g. \"find\", \"setstripe\", \"setquota\") that could use similar treatment, if you are interested.",
