      "date": "2011-05-19 04:52:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Tests 204{a,e,f,g,h} need to be fixed. Looking at the\n> results from the upatched tests, they falsely reported\n> a pass. I will do this in another patch.\n\nNote that we cannot land a patch if it fails testing, so if\nthis patch introduces a test failure it needs to be fixed\nin the context of this patch as well, rather than a separate\npatch.\n\nThat said, I'm not clear that there is a problem with this\npatch.  \n\nIt is also not a good practice to make patches dependent\nupon each other if there is no hard dependency between them.\nAFAIK, it means that this simple patch cannot be landed\nuntil the ioctl and lfs getstripe patches have landed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "542494858647b49c7fc69e380e4c4312c9e509a6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-19 15:13:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nAndreas,\n\nThe failures and false passes I mentioned do not have to deal with this patch per se, rather with the LU-64 patch stack as a whole (i.e. the previous two patches this change depends on).\n\n\nOleg,\n\nThe tests I mentioned were fixed in c535. Although, that patch will be merged into the new rebased ioctl fix (c352).\n\nAnd yes I agree this patch should have been pushed separately from the other two patches.\n\nSince I am going to rebase the ioctl change (c352) with a different Change-Id, I might as well remove the dependencies for this patch and just rebase it on top master at the same time.. Unless I get any objections soon, I will go ahead and do this.\n\nHopefully that will make it easier to inspect and land.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "4619695e2f539fd71aeef1f8d89f53f6c42e143e",
